#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn8.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn8.7:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Vaṅgīsavagga "
msgstr "1. With Vaṅgīsa "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn8.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Pavāraṇāsutta "
msgstr "7. The Invitation to Admonish "

# NOTE: Here we use monk for bhikkhu; as a formal sanghakamma, the bhikkhunis would not have been present.
#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.411, sc1
msgctxt "sn8.7:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi sabbeheva arahantehi. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Eastern Monastery, the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother, together with a large Saṅgha of around five hundred monks, all of whom were perfected ones. "

msgctxt "sn8.7:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā tadahuposathe pannarase pavāraṇāya bhikkhusaṅghaparivuto abbhokāse nisinno hoti. "
msgstr "Now, at that time it was the sabbath—the full moon on the fifteenth day—and the Buddha was sitting in the open surrounded by the Saṅgha of monks for the invitation to admonish. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.7:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tuṇhībhūtaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ anuviloketvā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha looked around the Saṅgha of monks, who were so very silent. He addressed them: "

msgctxt "sn8.7:1.4"
msgid "“handa dāni, bhikkhave, pavāremi vo. "
msgstr "“Come now, monks, I invite you all: "

msgctxt "sn8.7:1.5"
msgid "Na ca me kiñci garahatha kāyikaṃ vā vācasikaṃ vā”ti. "
msgstr "Is there anything I’ve done by way of body or speech that you would criticize?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.191, sc2
msgctxt "sn8.7:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, Venerable Sāriputta got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said: "

msgctxt "sn8.7:2.2"
msgid "“na kho mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavato kiñci garahāma kāyikaṃ vā vācasikaṃ vā. "
msgstr "“There is nothing, sir, that you’ve done by way of body or speech that we would criticize. "

msgctxt "sn8.7:2.3"
msgid "Bhagavā hi, bhante, anuppannassa maggassa uppādetā, asañjātassa maggassa sañjanetā, anakkhātassa maggassa akkhātā, maggaññū maggavidū maggakovido. "
msgstr "For the Blessed One is the one who gave rise to the unarisen path, who gave birth to the unborn path, who explained the unexplained path. He is the knower of the path, the discoverer of the path, the expert on the path. "

msgctxt "sn8.7:2.4"
msgid "Maggānugā ca, bhante, etarahi sāvakā viharanti pacchā samannāgatā; "
msgstr "And now the disciples live following the path; they acquire it later. "

msgctxt "sn8.7:2.5"
msgid "ahañca kho, bhante, bhagavantaṃ pavāremi. "
msgstr "And sir, I invite the Blessed One. "

msgctxt "sn8.7:2.6"
msgid "Na ca me bhagavā kiñci garahati kāyikaṃ vā vācasikaṃ vā”ti. "
msgstr "Is there anything I’ve done by way of body or speech that you would criticize?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.412, sc3
msgctxt "sn8.7:3.1"
msgid "“Na khvāhaṃ te, sāriputta, kiñci garahāmi kāyikaṃ vā vācasikaṃ vā. "
msgstr "“There is nothing, Sāriputta, that you’ve done by way of body or speech that I would criticize. "

msgctxt "sn8.7:3.2"
msgid "Paṇḍito tvaṃ, sāriputta, mahāpañño tvaṃ, sāriputta, puthupañño tvaṃ, sāriputta, hāsapañño tvaṃ, sāriputta, javanapañño tvaṃ, sāriputta, tikkhapañño tvaṃ, sāriputta, nibbedhikapañño tvaṃ, sāriputta. "
msgstr "Sāriputta, you are astute. You have great wisdom, widespread wisdom, laughing wisdom, swift wisdom, sharp wisdom, penetrating wisdom. "

msgctxt "sn8.7:3.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, rañño cakkavattissa jeṭṭhaputto pitarā pavattitaṃ cakkaṃ sammadeva anuppavatteti; "
msgstr "A wheel-turning monarch’s oldest son rightly keeps wielding the power set in motion by his father. "

msgctxt "sn8.7:3.4"
msgid "evameva kho tvaṃ, sāriputta, mayā anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavattitaṃ sammadeva anuppavattesī”ti. "
msgstr "In the same way, Sāriputta rightly keeps rolling the supreme Wheel of Dhamma that was rolled forth by me.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn8.7:4.1"
msgid "“No ce kira me, bhante, bhagavā kiñci garahati kāyikaṃ vā vācasikaṃ vā. "
msgstr "“Since it seems I have done nothing worthy of the Blessed One’s criticism, "

msgctxt "sn8.7:4.2"
msgid "Imesaṃ pana, bhante, bhagavā pañcannaṃ bhikkhusatānaṃ na kiñci garahati kāyikaṃ vā vācasikaṃ vā”ti. "
msgstr "is there anything these five hundred monks have done by way of body or speech that you would criticize?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.7:4.3"
msgid "“Imesampi khvāhaṃ, sāriputta, pañcannaṃ bhikkhusatānaṃ na kiñci garahāmi kāyikaṃ vā vācasikaṃ vā. "
msgstr "“There is nothing, Sāriputta, that these five hundred monks have done by way of body or speech that I would criticize. "

msgctxt "sn8.7:4.4"
msgid "Imesañhi, sāriputta, pañcannaṃ bhikkhusatānaṃ saṭṭhi bhikkhū tevijjā, saṭṭhi bhikkhū chaḷabhiññā, saṭṭhi bhikkhū ubhatobhāgavimuttā, atha itare paññāvimuttā”ti. "
msgstr "For of these five hundred monks, sixty have the three knowledges, sixty have the six direct knowledges, sixty are freed both ways, and the rest are freed by wisdom.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.413, sc5
msgctxt "sn8.7:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā vaṅgīso uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Vaṅgīsa got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said, "

msgctxt "sn8.7:5.2"
msgid "“paṭibhāti maṃ, bhagavā, paṭibhāti maṃ, sugatā”ti. "
msgstr "“I feel inspired to speak, Blessed One! I feel inspired to speak, Holy One!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.7:5.3"
msgid "“Paṭibhātu taṃ, vaṅgīsā”ti bhagavā avoca. "
msgstr "“Then speak as you feel inspired,” said the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.7:5.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā vaṅgīso bhagavantaṃ sammukhā sāruppāhi gāthāhi abhitthavi: "
msgstr "Then Vaṅgīsa extolled the Buddha in his presence with fitting verses: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn8.7:6.1"
msgid "“Ajja pannarase visuddhiyā, "
msgstr "“Today, on the fifteenth day sabbath, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.7:6.2"
msgid "Bhikkhū pañcasatā samāgatā; "
msgstr "five hundred monks have gathered together to purify their precepts. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.7:6.3"
msgid "Saṃyojanabandhanacchidā, "
msgstr "These untroubled sages have cut off their fetters and bonds, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.7:6.4"
msgid "Anīghā khīṇapunabbhavā isī. "
msgstr "they will not be reborn again. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.192, sc7
msgctxt "sn8.7:7.1"
msgid "Cakkavattī yathā rājā, "
msgstr "Just as a wheel-turning monarch "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.7:7.2"
msgid "amaccaparivārito; "
msgstr "surrounded by ministers "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.7:7.3"
msgid "Samantā anupariyeti, "
msgstr "travels all around this "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.7:7.4"
msgid "sāgarantaṃ mahiṃ imaṃ. "
msgstr "land that’s girt by sea. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn8.7:8.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vijitasaṅgāmaṃ, "
msgstr "So disciples with the three knowledges, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.7:8.2"
msgid "satthavāhaṃ anuttaraṃ; "
msgstr "destroyers of death, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.7:8.3"
msgid "Sāvakā payirupāsanti, "
msgstr "revere the winner of the battle, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.7:8.4"
msgid "tevijjā maccuhāyino. "
msgstr "the unsurpassed caravan leader. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.414, sc9
msgctxt "sn8.7:9.1"
msgid "Sabbe bhagavato puttā, "
msgstr "All are sons of the Blessed One—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.7:9.2"
msgid "palāpettha na vijjati; "
msgstr "there is no rubbish here. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.7:9.3"
msgid "Taṇhāsallassa hantāraṃ, "
msgstr "I bow to the Kinsman of the Sun, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn8.7:9.4"
msgid "vande ādiccabandhunan”ti. "
msgstr "destroyer of the dart of craving.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
